# Personal Finance Analysis (Excel / Google Sheets)

## Project Status
In progress. This project uses one personal finance dataset and is progressively
improved while learning Excel / Google Sheets fundamentals.

## Objective
To analyze personal finance data and understand income, expenses, and spending patterns.

## Dataset
Personal finance dataset sourced from Kaggle.
Used for learning and portfolio purposes.

## Learning Approach
This project uses a single dataset.
The same data is re-analyzed multiple times as new skills are learned.

## Tools
- Google Sheets (analysis)
- GitHub (documentation)

## Learning Log
This project is being built step by step.
Each section is updated as I learn new skills.

## Data Understanding
The dataset contains personal finance transactions including date, amount,
transaction type (income or expense), category, and account used.
The goal at this stage is to understand what questions the data can answer
before deeper analysis.

## Steps Completed
- Opened and reviewed dataset
- Checked for empty cells
- Cleaned basic data issues
- Created pivot tables
- Explored charts

## Next Steps
- Review data types and formatting
- Perform structured data cleaning
- Rebuild pivot tables step by step
- Create final charts
- Add insights and conclusions
- Finalize charts
- Save visuals
- Upload cleaned dataset
- Add insights
